HEART DISEASE DIAGNOSTIC ANALYSIS¶

The Goal of this project is to analyse the heart disease accurence,based on a combination of features that describe the heart disease.

I will use Python to perform all the data analysis and visualization. I start with importing the necessary modules for this project:Pandas,Numpy,Matplotlib.

Then the dataset is imported into the environment through the read.csv method.

In [10]:
df.columns
Out[10]:
Index(['age', 'sex', 'cp', 'trestbps', 'chol', 'fbs', 'restecg', 'thalach',
       'exang', 'oldpeak', 'slope', 'ca', 'thal', 'target'],
      dtype='object')

There are thirteen feature in Dataset
age:The pearson's age in years
sex:The Pearson's sex(1=Male,0=Female)
cp:The chest pain experienced(Value 1:typical angina, Value2:atypical angina, Value 3:non-anginal pain,Value4:asympotomatic)
trestbps:The person's resting blood pressure(mm Hg on admission to the hospital)
chol:The person's cholestrol measurement in mg/dl
fbs:The person's fasting blood sugar(>120 mg/dl,1=true;0=false)
restecg:Resting electrocardiographic measurment (0=normal,1=havingST-T wave abnormality,2=showing proble or definite left ventricular
thalach:The person's maximum heart rate achieved
exang:Exercise induced angina(1=yes;0=no)
oldpeak:ST depression induced by exercise relative to rest slope:The slope of the peak exercise ST segment (Value1:upsioping,Value2:flat,Value3:downsloping)
ca:The number of major vessel(0-3)
thal:A blood disorder called thalassemia(3=normal;6=fixed defect;7=reversable defect)
num:Heart disease(0=no,1=yes)

def heart_d(r):
    if r==0:
        return 'Absence'
    elif r==1:
        return 'Presence'
In [11]:
df['Heart_Disease']=df['target'].apply(heart_d)

def age_rng(r):
    if r>=29 and r<40:
        return 'young Age'
    elif r>=40 and r<55:
        return 'Middle Age'
    elif r>55:
        return 'Elder Age'
In [16]:

#heatmap cration using seaborn
df.dtypes
numeric_data=df.select_dtypes(include=['float64','int64'])
numeric_data=numeric_data.fillna(numeric_data.median())
correlation_matrix=numeric_data.corr()
plt.figure(figsize=(12,8))
sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix,annot=True,cmap='coolwarm',linewidths=0.5)
plt.title('Correlation Heat Map For Heart Disease ',fontsize=17)
plt.show()
